1. cluster authentication operator
The Operator is a piece of software running in a Pod on the cluster, interacting with the Kubernetes API server. It is deployed by k8s api and run to manage k8s objects. 
```
oc get clusteroperator authentication -o yaml
```

2. CustomResourceDefinition 
```
oc get crd authentications.operator.openshift.io -o yaml
```

3. Get the auth operator deployment 
```
oc get deployments authentication-operator -n openshift-authentication-operator -o yaml
```

4. Oauth config
```
oc describe configmap oauth-openshift -o openshift-config-managed
```


https://www.openshift.com/learn/topics/operators
https://github.com/openshift/cluster-authentication-operator
